cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with human face-based biometrics, specifically gender classification and age estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a learning framework that incorporates a semantic relationship between gender and age, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses SVM and ordinal regression methods, which are common in machine learning, further supporting the possibility of cs.LG. The paper also mentions kernelized nonlinear counterparts, which could suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on three aging datasets, which could suggest cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible categories.
